<TEXT>
the man suspected of killing a family of 
four and setting their bodies on fire christmas weekend died from 
police gunfire rather than a selfinflicted wound according to 
autopsy results released thursday 
michael kinge also known as anthony turner died wednesday 
morning in a shootout with state police when they tried to arrest 
him at his dryden apartment 
police opened fire on kinge when he turned toward them and fired 
the shotgun he had been holding under his chin it hadnt been 
immediately clear whether kinge 33 died from his own or police 
bullets 
state police capt carl shaver said the tompkins county medical 
examiner found that kinge died as a result of police bullets the 
shot he fired grazed the left side of his face but wasnt fatal 
shaver said 
a coroners investigation ruled the death justifiable 
homicide shaver said 
the medical examiners believed he was turning to fire at 
police and his gun accidentally discharged shaver said 
kinge would have been charged with the dec 22 killings of 
dolores and warren a harris and their two children 15yearold 
shelby and 11yearold marc 
the harrises were each bound hand and foot shot in the back of 
the head and then doused with gasoline and set afire robbery is 
believed to be the motive and police traced kinge through 
descriptions of a man who used credit cards stolen from the family 
home 
police said that a sawedoff rifle found in the suspects 
apartment had been positively identified as the weapon used to kill 
the family 
kinges mother 54yearold shirley kinge has been charged with 
four counts of seconddegree murder one count of arson and one 
count of possessing stolen property in the harris case 
