<TEXT>
doctors at johns hopkins hospital will be 
randomly tested for alcohol and drugs under a policy initiated by 
the physicians themselves the hospital said thursday 
hopkins was believed to be the first hospital in the country to 
adopt such a policy for physicians 
dr hamilton moses iii the hospitals vice president for 
medical affairs said the policy will take effect in july twenty 
percent to 50 percent of the 750 doctors who are up for 
reappointment then would be randomly selected for tests to 
determine if they have used alcohol tranquilizers cocaine or 
other drugs he said 
we dont know the precise number and weve not actually 
devised the precise protocol that we will be using but we expect 
to screen somewhere between a quarter and a half of the medical 
staff every other year moses said 
under the policy doctors who test positive for drugs or alcohol 
would be tested a second time after a second positive test they 
would be evaluated and if necessary sent for rehabilitation 
hospital spokeswoman joann rodgers said 
onlyif the doctor is not successfully rehabilitated would 
he be dismissed or removed from the staff moses said 
objections to our plan have been raised moses said not 
every person perceives there is a need to do it and not everyone on 
the staff believes its appropriate to be this heavyhanded 
officials with the american hospital association and american 
medical association said they were unaware of any hospital 
instituting such a policy for doctors 
there are hospitals who do testing on employees and it is 
common to have for cause kinds of drug tests but no one here is 
aware of a regular community or acute care hospital that tests 
physicians said mary babich spokewoman for the american hospital 
association 
the american medical associations policy on drug testing of 
doctors is under review a spokesman said thursday 
nonclinical faculty at hopkins who dont care directly for 
patients are exempt from random testing testing for them and 
others in the school of medicine is under review rodgers said 
doctors and other hospital workers such as nurses and 
technicians are subject to a threeyearold policy that requires 
tests if supervisors believe an employees work has been impaired 
by drugs or alcohol rodgers said 
all physicians involved in direct patient care most of whom are 
up for reappointment after two years will be tested every two 
years rodgers said 
everybody eventually will be tested probably within the 
twoyear time period after that everybody will be tested each 
time they come up for credentialing or renewal she said 
hopkins has a medical staff of 1500 
</TEXT>
