<TEXT>
with the wrecking ball just off stage left the 
curtain is going down on little jack horner jokes and magic home 
for half a century to pranksters clowns and vaudevillian wannabees 
little jack horners regulars say they are losing an informal 
clubhouse and that boston is losing a little bit of its heart 
people come in here not just to shop said owner fred 
lezburg weve got second and thirdgeneration customers who 
remember coming here as kids 
and of course there are the characters 
we get a lot of them lezburg says 
there are those who wander in to check out the pranks designed 
for an adult audience or the groups of giggling young women who 
come in on their lunch break looking for just the right prop for a 
bachelorette party 
but lezburg says the clowns who are not the biggest spenders 
but regular and fun will probably end up the hardest hit 
theyll have to look elsewhere for their oversized scissors rubber 
noses and other crowdpleasers 
gone too will be the inflatable wayne newton dolls whoopie 
cushions and exploding cigars say goodbye to the rubber chickens 
and counterfeit cockroaches things that squirt and pop out of cans 
say goodbye as a matter of fact to an entire block of one of 
bostons most colorful little streets which runs down the hill 
from the state capitol building the buildings owner wants to put 
a new face on the street tear down the building and put up an 
office tower 
also caught up in the change will be bromfield streets hat 
cleaning and shine where a customer could get a good shine for a 
buck or so and where theyd even put new heels on your shoes if 
you wanted to wait a few minutes also affected are a flower shop 
and a jeweler specializing in pawn 
they want a bigger better higher building said lezburg a 
reformed accountant who took over the business nearly five 
years ago and i guess we dont fit into the picture 
the picture in downtown boston has changed a lot in recent 
years rundown blocks are revitalized while the fabled strip joints 
and back alley bars of the nearby combat zone fade slowly from 
the scene 
and as often is the case the momandpop stores that dotted 
narrow streets are giving way to bigger stores and office buildings 
this street has become a dead end lezburg said wednesday 
and its too bad because this is a place that a lot of people 
look to as being the high point of their day 
starting today the prices on lezburgs stock were going to be 
slashed when the skyhigh shelves lined with rubber likenesses of 
everyone from ronald reagan to horror movie character freddie 
krueger are cleared the city will have only one joke store on 
which to rely jacks joke shop 
founded in 1922 it claims to be the nations oldest active joke 
shop 
im quite sure that down the line people will come into my 
shop and ask where did little jack horners go said harold 
bengin who took over jacks joke shop from his fatherinlaw 
and sadly ill have to say theyve gone out of business its 
tough for the little guy in todays economy 
until about two weeks ago lezburg had been trying to find a 
place to relocate but hes paying about 20 a square foot on 
bromfield street and prices like that have gone the way of his 
hardtofind 200 planet of the apes mask and besides lezburg has 
gone through this before and isnt convinced it wouldnt happen 
again 
in 1986 he was forced out of little jack horners original site 
around the corner near boston common to make way for a condominium 
project 
this is the kind of store that lends itself to laughter and 
im trying to keep that up on the outside lezburg said but on 
the inside im not doing as well i put my heart into this thing 
and im coming up empty and disappointed terribly disappointed 
