<TEXT>
in the countrys most sweeping 
crackdown on illegal pornography police have seized more than 
200000 adult sex magazines worth 73 million and arrested at 
least 18 people prosecutors said today 
more than 20000 of the magazines were copies of playboy 
penthouse and hustler stolen from a us army base in seoul 
prosecutors said the magazines are not available legally in south 
korea but are sold to us forces through base outlets 
blackmarket copies sell for 22 to 30 apiece 
the seoul district prosecutors office said that among 
koreanproduced materials in the seizure were 50000 comic books 
depicting explicit sex 15000 magazines with erotic pictures and 
text 10000 pornographic books and 5000 sex gadgets and 
stimulants 
nah myongsu 49 and ahn dokjun 41 who helped run the 
warehouse for the us 8th army in seoul were charged with larceny 
and illegally handing over to third parties copies of magazines 
pilfered from the warehouse since 1983 
prosecutor cho chungung said charges against other people were 
for producing and marketing obscene publications and sex gadgets 
and illegally dealing in pornographic materials he said the 
investigation into organized criminal rings which specialize in 
underground sex was continuing 
on wednesday prosecutors announced the arrest of nine people 
including a department store president a film star and a runnerup 
in the miss korea pageant for allegedly using illegal drugs in sex 
orgies 
south korea is a conservative homogeneous society with 
oldfashioned values of family marriage and centuriesold 
traditions many koreans are deeply concerned that their countrys 
increasing affluence and new westernstyle consumerism are tearing 
at the social fabric 
the government has stepped up efforts in the past year to weed 
out illicit drugs pornography and prostitution arrests have been 
made but such activities continue to thrive 
