<TEXT>
bobbi bloks voice is barely above a whisper 
as she tries to explain why she hasnt eaten any food in more than 
five weeks she appears somewhat disoriented and apologizes for 
allowing her thoughts to wander and being unable to express herself 
clearly 
blok 36 views her fast from jan 1 to feb 14 as her share 
of the war against drugs 
the problems facing children and the family in the country 
are at a crisis situation and drugs are the reason says blok 
executive director of a child advocacy group the washington child 
development center something has got to be done 
blok is drinking only a glass of grape juice in the morning and 
water through the rest of the day the purpose of the fast is 
twofold to bring about a local and national drug summit and to 
get the government to increase funding to battle the drug problem 
at the social level not in law enforcement 
blok plans to end her fast on valentines day because she 
believes this country has a heart 
she said she is grateful she was cleansing herself when 
washington mayor marion barry was arrested for possession of 
cocaine on jan 18 blok a senior campaign aide for barry in 1986 
said she never saw barry use drugs 
he did however have the symptoms of a drug user she said 
i made it clear to the mayor that i felt he needed help she 
said it was three days before christmas here was the mayor a 
friend who needed help and rather than confronting him i had 
been accepting his lessthanadequate explanations of his 
activities 
barry had all the classic forms of denial in that he was 
saying one thing and doing another he had his priorities 
distorted and i blame drugs she added 
so far her hunger strike has not brought about the government 
policy changes she seeks but blok says she remains undaunted and 
doesnt believe she has starved herself for nothing 
im losing my stamina but in terms of my resolve and my 
commitment its never been stronger she said in an interview 
tuesday i feel like theres a reason im doing this if only to 
even strengthen my belief in knowing that an individual has the 
power to deal with the problems that face our society 
i do not feel as if ive been ignored i realize that im 
risking my life that cant be denied but ive gotten to the 
point where i cant sit still and watch our elected officials deny 
that there is a drug epidemic 
she has asked her physician not to tell her how much weight she 
has lost and she is undergoing a blood test at least once a week 
blok said she started the fast after learning of a drugrelated 
killing at an unlicensed child care center a few days later while 
she was working as a substitute at a day care center she overheard 
3yearold children talking about drugs the police and guns 
i have to believe that people care about this blok said 
i also believe that our president cares but what good is reading 
his lips if theres no substance to what he says something has got 
to be done about this drug situation the real victims of the 
drug war are our children 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

