<DOCNO> AP900208-0012 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
an epidemic of delays and baggage problems are 
plaguing the nations airlines but theyre getting fewer 
complaints according to a government report 
ontime performance for december dipped to 702 percent from the 
78 percent reported in november the transportation department air 
travel consumer report said wednesday 
the worst previous showing was in january 1988 when 692 percent 
of flights were reported on time 
the department blamed heavy holiday travel and severe winter 
weather in some parts of the country for service disruptions at the 
nations largest airports delays due to mechanical problems are 
not included in the report 
mishandled baggage complaints filed against the carriers nearly 
doubled from 699 per 1000 passengers in november to 1278 per 
1000 passengers in december it was the worst month since the 
department began reporting airline performance two years ago 
complaints for 1989 totalled 12403 which was about half the 
number received in 1988 
continuing the downward trend december complaints totalled 749 
down 33 percent from the 1125 logged in november and the lowest 
since december 1989 when there were 733 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

