<TEXT>
nonwhite americans were more interested than 
whites in bostons charles stuart murder case the arrest of 
washington mayor marion barry and the mcmartin child abuse 
acquittal according to a survey of interest in the news 
among all people white and nonwhite the crash of an avianca 
airlines plane on long island topped the monthly interest index of 
the times mirror center for the people and the press 
news of the crash of the colombian airliner in which more than 
70 people died was followed closely by 33 percent of those 
surveyed 
among nonwhites however 31 percent paid close attention to 
the avianca crash compared with 44 percent for the story of 
stuart who took his life amid allegations that he had murdered his 
wife and tried to blame it on a black man 
twentyseven percent of whites followed the stuart story 
closely and that case was more interesting to women than to men by 
34 percent to 23 percent 
overall the case was second in interest with 29 percent 
followed by 28 percent for barrys arrest on a drug charge and 27 
percent for the acquittal of the owners of the mcmartin day care 
center in california 
since the survey of 1245 adults is subject to a 3 percent 
error the stuart barry and mcmartin stories were virtually tied 
among nonwhites the arrest of washingtons black mayor on a 
drug charge attracted the close interest of 41 percent compared 
with 26 percent for whites the mcmartin story also held more 
interest for nonwhites than for whites 36 percent to 26 percent 
news of nelson mandelas impending release from jail in south 
africa was of close interest to 26 percent of nonwhites compared 
with only 9 percent of whites 
however since that story erupted in the midst of interviewing 
for the february index there are too few respondents who were 
asked to rate their attention to south africa to enable a reliable 
test of the significance of the racial difference in interest 
times mirror said 
the center said there have only been 11 stories since it 
started the surveys in 1986 in which news interest has been 
affected by race others included the letter bombings of federal 
judges elections of black political leaders and racial violence in 
virginia beach va 
the study also said 22 percent of americans followed the super 
bowl professional football game very closely and six out of 10 
watched it on television four out of 10 watched president bushs 
state of the union address 
forty percent of those surveyed could identify barry as 
washingtons mayor 56 percent knew mandela was an imprisoned black 
leader in south africa 
times mirror is a los angelesbased media company that publishes 
the los angeles times newsday and new york newsday the baltimore 
sun newspapers the hartford courant national journal and 
broadcasting magazine among other journals it also engages in 
broadcasting and cable television book publishing and specialized 
information and training businesses 
