could not use an 1866 law to press her claim ruling the statute 
barred only hiring discrimination not harassment once a person was 
on the job 
force employers to show that any practice with proven 
discriminatory impact was prompted by business necessity the court 
ruled that the burden of proof belongs with workers who allege they 
are the victims of bias 
make clear that it is always illegal to use race ethnicity 
gender or religion as a motivating factor in employment decisions 
the supreme court ruling on that subject was vague enough to 
confuse lower courts 
