designed to remedy discrimination the court made it easier for 
white men to challenge such plans years after they are put into 
effect 
ease the deadlines for workers who sue over allegedly biased 
seniority systems the court ruled that the time for filing such 
lawsuits is determined by when a seniority plan is adopted not 
when an individual worker is affected 
assure victims of intentional discrimination the right to sue 
for monetary damages 
