the decision of communist leaders to give up their 
monopoly on power has met only one demand of citizens who are 
hostages to an economy that is slipping from chaos to catastrophe 
the move wednesday by the partys policymaking central 
committee attacks the most visible targets middlelevel party 
officials who have long been under pressure from mikhail s 
gorbachev and now feel heat from below 
but it will take some time to change the stalinist structure and 
centrally orchestrated decisionmaking mechanism that put those 
officials in power and allowed the economy to sink slowly into 
disarray 
the changes will depend on gorbachevs success in attracting new 
people who are honest innovative and able to gain the peoples 
confidence 
gorbachev is gambling he can find the right people in the 
communist party and keep them there 
his risk is that the apparatus now apparently on its way out has 
so damaged the partys credibility that the people he needs will 
