<TEXT>
a tankers hull was gashed and 
hundreds of thousands of gallons of heavy alaskan crude oil spewed 
from the ship wednesday two miles off a popular southern california 
beach officials said 
early reports indicated that more than 290000 gallons of north 
slope crude spilled from the fully loaded 811foot american trader 
according to coast guard rear adm william kime 
hours after the 435 pm accident the leading edge of the 
1mile long oil slick was headed toward several recreational 
beaches and a wildlife estuary surrounding the huntington beach 
harbor coast guard officials said 
those wetlands and wildlife preserves are so very precious 
said dorothy green president of heal the bay a local 
environmental group 
the coast guard initially reported the tanker had struck a 
submerged pipeline but huntington beach spokesman dave kelly said 
the ship was punctured by its own anchor 
as the ship was docking the anchor swung back into the bow 
breaching the forward compartment kelly said 
coast guard cmdr scott porter assistant chief of marine 
safety couldnt confirm kellys report 
a diver found a 3foot hole in the bottom of the tankers no 1 
forward compartment which holds more than 1 million gallons of 
crude coast guard capt james card told reporters late wednesday 
no other damage was found 
the tankers captain who was not identified would be tested 
for alcohol and drug use as a routine part of the investigation 
card said 
coast guard officials expected the oil would foul huntington 
city beach huntington state beach and chica bolsa state beach an 
environmentally sensitive marsh behind chica bolsa clearly is 
threatened porter said 
at this time of the year what we know is that the currents 
would carry it in toward the beach toward the northwest porter 
said 
the spilled crude was the same kind as the oil that fouled 
