an emergency response team of local state and federal officials 
was being convened by telephone to discuss the emergency said 
kime commander of the 11th coast guard district 
the american trader was leased by british petroleum oil shipping 
co usa said joe braderich manager of the firms los angeles 
field office it is operated by american trading transportation co 
inc of new york city 
the tanker was on a final approach maneuver in about 80 feet of 
water to hook up with a mooring buoy when it struck something 
braderich said after the tanker is secured to the buoy the crew 
usually connects to a pipeline hauled up from the ocean bottom to 
pump its cargo ashore he added 
the ships draft when fully loaded is about 40 feet said 
american trading president sanford schmidt 
the tanker was carrying about 500000 barrels or 21 million 
gallons in its 10 hull tanks said schmidt the compartment that 
was breached carries about 25000 barrels or about 1050000 
gallons 
any spill over 100000 gallons is considered major kime said 
british petroleum has assumed responsibility for the spill the 
admiral said 
the spill occurred just off huntington beach a city about 30 
miles south of los angeles long popular with southern california 
surfers and sunbathers and often the scene for movies and 
television shows featuring surfing 
a city police helicopter crew estimated the slick from the spill 
was about 300 feet wide and 1 miles long said city lifeguard 
capt william richardson it stretched from the ship to an area 
north of the pier a distance of about 12 blocks 
the mooring buoy serves as an offloading point for an oil 
