<TEXT>
erich honecker kept a private stash of 60 
million into which the former east german communist leader dipped 
to make special purchases such as a watch once owned by vladimir 
i lenin prosecutors said 
the countrys deputy chief prosecutor lothar reuter on 
wednesday read an astonishing list of the extravagances and corrupt 
activities allegedly committed by communist party officials during 
honeckers 18year rule 
he said that during 40 years of communist rule corruption was 
rampant but that prosecutors still have not uncovered all the 
details 
honeckers private account on any given day contained about 60 
million reuter said most of it supplied by a former official 
accused of arranging illegal arms exports 
honecker once used 454000 from such an account to buy a the 
lenin pocket watch reuter alleged 
the former leader ousted oct 18 in a peaceful popular revolt 
also apparently had his generous side 
sometimes just before christmas he would bless the people 
by arranging purchases of bananas nearly nonexistent in east 
germany reuter charged that at such moments honecker was trying 
to play santa claus of the nation being bilked by communist 
officials 
he said leading officers of the state security service were 
stealing western currency sent through the mail to east german 
citizens from west german friends and relatives in the last three 
years alone more than 4 million was pilfered in this fashion he 
alleged 
honecker 77 and a number of his lieutenants are awaiting trial 
on a broad range of charges from high treason to human rights 
violations to misuse of public funds 
the former leader was arrested last week and sent to prison but 
he was released a day later after doctors determined he was too 
frail to withstand detention 
authorities announced wednesday that honecker will be indicted 
for high treason in march and tried before the countrys supreme 
court he could face life in prison if convicted 
many of honeckers former lieutenants are in jail and also will 
stand trial such as expremier willi stoph ousted economics chief 
guenther mittag and fired security chief erich mielke 
reuter said honecker and other communists who have been 
interrogated for criminal acts seem to show little remorse 
most of the accused have either a slight sense of guilt or 
none at all reuter told reporters by and large they are not 
ready to assume responsibility for the immense squandering of 
public wealth 
reuter said honeckers private accounts were kept filled with 
western currency by alexander schalckgolodkowski east germanys 
former chief foreign trader who has fled the country 
schalckgolodkowski has been accused of overseeing an illegal 
weapons depot to export arms and earn western currency for east 
germanys leaders 
police found 24760 machine pistols 1398 automatic rifles 
1691 revolvers six bazookas 502 hand grenades and a vast number 
of bullets when they raided the depot in december the official adn 
news agency said wednesday 
mielke once had a mansion built for 606000 but never used it 
said reuter nonetheless mielke kept the house supplied with power 
and it was looked after daily according to reuter 
a total of 134000 was paid annually to heat stophs private 
greenhouses said reuter 
he also told of top communist party officials who would help 
themselves to videocassette recorders and other expensive 
electronic goods seized by customs authorities 
reuter said prosecutors across east germany have been 
overwhelmed with work on the corruption cases he did not reveal 
how many arrests have been made or say how many trials might be 
held 
there are hundreds of cases like this across the country he 
said 
