the federal government is proposing stiff 
fines for private group that imply in their advertising or 
solicitations that their services are sanctioned by social security 
or medicare programs 
the department of health and human services proposed the 
regulation wednesday in response to the many complaints it has 
received about such false assertions 
the proposal would cover misuse of the terms social 
security social security account social security 
administration social security system medicare and 
health care financing administration or the letters ssa or 
hcfa 
use of any symbols or emblems associated with either the social 
security administration or the health care financing administration 
also would be a violation 
under the proposed regulation which is subject to a time for 
public comment before being adopted the department could impose a 
civil fines of up to 25000 per violation for a misleading tv or 
radio broadcast and up to 5000 for violations occurring in print 
advertising 
