on friday to help pay burial expenses 
the girls identity and details of her condition had been kept 
private at her familys request until a texas newspaper identified 
her and her father atrell harvey ii an employee of the campbell 
soup co with the familys permission madden confirmed her 
identity wednesday 
the disease mimi suffered from has a variety of causes and is 
characterized by an inability of the lungs to transfer oxygen to 
the blood in its most severe forms it is fatal in 9095 percent of 
all cases madden said 
the ivox designed to give damaged lungs time to rest and 
recover is inserted via the neck or groin into the inferior vena 
cava the large vein that brings blood to the heart 
two tubes the diameter of a soda straw are attached to the 
bundle of tubes and lead out of the body one delivers oxygen to 
the blood the other removes carbon dioxide 
the food and drug administration approved ivox in september for 
temporary implantation in up to 10 people at lds penn state 
universitys hershey medical center the university of michigan 
medical center in ann arbor and the los angeles countyuniversity 
of southern california medical center 
before mimi died it was unclear how long doctors intended to 
leave the device inside her madden had said any use beyond the 
seven days would require fda permission 
mortensen said further implants will involve only patients with 
acute lung diseases not chronic disorders such as cystic fibrosis 
or emphysema 
were just waiting for the right case at any one of the 
centers he said 
