a 17yearold girl who has suffered 
memory lapses since a sports accident a year ago was found safe 
here today eight days after she disappeared from her wisconsin 
hometown hundreds of miles away 
michelle ebeling of janesville wis was picked up along an 
interstate highway around dawn by a truck driver who took her to a 
truck stop and called authorities police said 
sheriffs officials notified miss ebelings family ending the 
search that included more than a 1000 volunteers she had no idea 
of how she got to north carolina said her father tim ebeling 
were absolutely elated and thankful we all cried like 
fools said miss ebelings aunt ellie bickel we all talked to 
her and reassured her that we loved her very much 
the high school senior apparently wandered away last wednesday 
while waiting for a bus at craig high school 
the girl was an honors student and athlete before an injury 
during track practice last april left her partially paralyzed with 
shortterm memory loss and tunnel vision 
her family said she could remember the past and recognize family 
and friends but often would forget a request made 10 minutes 
before her therapy included carrying a book to write down what she 
needed to remember 
volunteers in the janesville area mounted a ground and air 
search over the weekend the family offered a 10000 reward and 
distributed about 60000 leaflets across the country 
when she was found the girl was wearing a long coat not the 
high school letter jacket she had on when she disappeared and 
carried no identification 
leah booe a sheriffs dispatcher said the trucker thought it 
was unusual for a young woman to be walking along the road at that 
hour and offered a ride 
richard jorgensen principal at her high school said the eight 
days of searching had affected everyone in the comunity of 51000 
he said a homecoming celebration will be held when michelle returns 
its been a week of deep concern caring frustration and just a 
matter of not knowing what you can do and wanting to do 
something he said 
mrs bickel said the girls parents would fly to north carolina 
and return with their daughter on friday 
