<TEXT>
here is a list of 10 of the worst oil spills in 
us history according to golobs oil pollution bulletin which 
has kept records since 1976 
1 march 24 1989 exxon valdez prince william sound alaska 
1092 million gallons of crude spilled when the ship ran aground 
2 nov 1 1979 burmah agate tanker galveston bay texas up 
to 107 million gallons of oil burned or spilled when two ships 
collided 
3 dec 15 1976 argo merchant tanker massachusetts southeast 
coast 76 million gallons of crude spilled when the ship ran 
aground 
4 nov 6 1985 exploratory well ranger texas 63 million 
gallons of oil spilled after a blowout 
5 jan 2 1988 ashland oil co aboveground storage tank 
jefferson borough pa 38 million gallons of oil spilled when a 
tank ruptured 
6 july 30 1984 alvenus tanker cameron la 28 million 
gallons of oil spilled after a ship ran aground 
7 oct 31 1984 puerto rican tanker san francisco 2 million 
gallons of oil spilled when a ship caught fire following an 
explosion 
8 aug 18 1984 triangle oil corp aboveground storage tank 
jacksonville fla 25 million gallons of oil burned after 
lightning sparked a fire 
9 nov 22 1980 georgia tanker pilottown la 13 million 
gallons of oil spilled after an anchor chain caused a ship to leak 
10 march 31 1982 arkas tanker montz la 147 million 
gallons of oil burned and spilled after a ship collision and fire 
</TEXT>
