to cut the long story short i will say only a few words to sum 
up the major discussion that was held in the hall of sessions of 
the party central committees plenums during the past three days 
i think that the discussion at the plenum on the entire range of 
issues was adequate to the dimension and novelty of the documents 
and problems that we discussed 
the plenum can be described in the following way it revealed 
the immense concern and immense anxiety of the central committee 
and the party in general over the situation in the country and in 
connection with the course of perestroika processes 
the plenum made a harsh critical analysis of all perestroika 
processes and forecast on its basis what is to be done and in what 
way this found reflection in the political guidelines that we 
placed at the basis of the soviet communist party central 
committees platform 
this is probably one more time after the work on resolutions of 
the 19th party conference that the entire central committee worked 
on the document in the sweat of its brow so to say i make the 
following very important conclusion all activity keenness and 
passions that emerged here all this reflects in one way or 
another the manifestation of concern about the party about the 
fate of perestroika and about giving correct political guidelines 
for society on the part of the ruling party at this very crucial 
stage of perestroika 
i think comrades that despite the diversity of views which 
was obvious at the plenum down to opposite positions that clashed 
here partially due to the lack of restraint this is all 
forgivable all comrades were unanimous that a progressive 
document was required a document that calls forward rather than 
backward in my opinion this is the dominant view 
i think that in some area of work there is a need to use some of 
the old mechanisms when new ones have not yet started working 
society should not be left rudderless and without sails without 
means that are able to advance perestroika in our huge country 
but the prevalent opinion which was endorsed in the soviet 
communist party central committees platform is that it is 
necessary to handle pressing problems along the tracks of 
perestroika renewal of society and renewal of the soviet communist 
party this is the main thing 
now one more thing or the reverse side of the medal i would 
say it is now not only by brain but literally by all skin do we 
feel that we must act resolutely the central committee the 
government and the supreme soviet should act 
i mention them not in order to give them instructions no we 
are expressing our position the main thing is that communists who 
are members of these bodies should act on the basis of this 
appraisal 
we cannot waste any more time it was fair to say to the party 
central committee it is inadmissible to be late now it is 
necessary to take the lead in stormy and complicated processes in 
order to support healthy trends consolidate them and try to 
overcome or inhibit destructive trends 
communists in the government should also act i think that 
comrades were right when they told party members working in the 
government that during the discussion of the platform at the plenum 
we did not hear their viewpoint 
it was said that there was such a discussion at the second 
congress of peoples deputies this is no argument it was 
necessary to have a discussion here as well the more so for the 
government is now handling practical things and it had what to say 
it was important for the central committee members to check 
these steps and orient the entire party to support and consolidate 
them above all to state our support for the program approved by 
the congress 
but i think that the government will find a way to inform 
central committee members and secretaries of party committees so 
that they clearly and fully realize all the specifics 
it is necessary to act in the supreme soviet from which major 
decisions are expected on key issues of perestroika and the 
improvement of the situation in the country communists should act 
vigorously and efficiently in all sectors in general we ought to 
consolidate forces by regrouping them and resolutely to advance 
perestroika and practical deeds 
the deeper we enter perestroika and explore all its strata the 
greater crystallization of positions and interests of opposing 
sides become we felt its presence here as well this is a 
reflection of the entire life of our society 
