a moraleboosting tour of strategic hills his troops seized from 
the militia this week at dbaye north of beirut 
his tele liban television station showed aoun in a dark blue 
beret flanked by a dozen heavily armed bodyguards talking to 
officers beside a demolished lebanese forces truck in dbaye 
the 54yearold general rarely leaves his bunker beneath the 
shattered presidential palace in baabda a christian suburb east of 
beirut he refuses to recognize president elias hrawi who fired 
him after being elected in november and has refused to leave the 
palace 
geagea a maronite catholic like aoun and hrawi said in a 
letter to pope john paul ii that aoun wanted to silence any voice 
that opposed his decisions 
aoun rejects a lebanese peace plan worked out last fall under 
arab league mediation which hrawi was elected to implement geagea 
recognizes hrawi as president but has not taken a public position 
on the peace agreement 
hundreds of people fled to west beirut from ashrafiyeh the 
militia stronghold that has seen the heaviest fighting but most 
residents of districts controlled by aoun appeared to be buying 
supplies and returning home 
