portauprince haiti ap haitis military government 
published on thursday an electoral law written by an independent 
panel one day after declaring a general amnesty and freeing 19 
political prisoners 
it includes all rules on balloting such as the number of 
polling stations to be set up who will staff them and where ballot 
boxes will be brought for the final tally under the constitution 
the electoral council has complete control over the voting process 
the ninemember electoral council appointed by such 
institutions as the roman catholic church labor unions and human 
rights groups has scheduled presidential elections for oct 28 
local elections are to be held april 29 and legislative elections 
on july 22 
a statement from the information ministry said lt gen prosper 
avrils government published the complete text that the members 
of the independent electoral council submitted to the executive 
most major politicians swore to boycott elections held under 
avril after a crackdown last month in which seven prominent leaders 
were exiled and more than 50 activists were arrested and allegedly 
beaten 
on wednesday night however the fourth anniversary of fallen 
dictator jeanclaude duvaliers flight into exile avril promised 
not to interfere in the electoral process and urged haitians to 
respect the rules of the democratic game 
he declared a general amnesty for 19 jailed activists 
implicated in crimes against national security 
at least four had been held since last year most of the others 
were believed to have been arrested during a nineday state of 
siege in january which followed the assassination of an army 
colonel 
avril lifted the state of siege on jan 29 and said exiled 
leaders could return most said they wont arguing that free 
elections are not possible under avril 
thugs protected by soldiers massacred at least 34 voters at 
polling stations in november 1987 causing cancellation of haitis 
first free general elections since independence from france in 1804 
lt gen henri namphy who took over when duvalier fled in 1986 
scheduled armyrun elections in january 1988 boycotted by most 
voters and candidates leslie manigat was declared winner but 
namphy ousted him five months later 
a soldiers revolt drove out namphy in september 1988 and 
brought avril to power in this impoverished caribbean island 
thousands of haitian expatriates in miami montreal guadeloupe 
and paris demonstrated wednesday to celebrate duvaliers ouster and 
demand avrils removal 
