in its latest effort to halt rioting in the 
occupied territories the israeli army has introduced a 
jeepmounted gravel thrower that spews out 600 eggsized rocks a 
minute israel radio said thursday 
it is the latest addition to the armys growing antiuprising 
arsenal that includes tear gas and rubber plastic and metal 
bullets 
israel has drawn international criticism for firing guns at 
stonethrowers most of them children and teenagers but army 
officials say troops use live ammunition only when their lives are 
in danger 
also on thursday a military source said the army will increase 
bail for palestinian stonethrowers under the age of 15 from 750 
to 2500 
the source speaking on condition of anonymity said the money 
will be returned with interest if the child does not repeat the 
offense within one year of his arrest 
