subfreezing temperatures were confin and an insurance industry 
group said thursday that a study of 106 former and current state 
insurance commissioners showed about half of them obtained jobs 
with insurance companies after they left office 
the study highlights the short period of time many 
commissioners served and the number of former commissioners who 
immediately moved to the industry after leaving office said 
stephen brobeck executive director of the consumer federation of 
america 
the study was released by the consumer insurance interest group 
and the national association of professional insurance agents 
which said state insurance commissioners should be prohibited from 
working directly or indirectly for the industry for one year after 
leaving office to avoid the reality or appearance of conflict of 
interest 
the survey found that 49 percent of the former commissioners 
worked for insurance companies or provided legal accounting or 
other professional services to the industry after leaving office 
their study is incomplete and does not support that sweeping 
conclusion said earle palmeroy president of the national 
association of insurance commissioners 
theyve made no conclusion that the regulation of individual 
commissioners was affected by their later work for the industry 
said palmeroy the north dakota commissioner 
palmeroy also objected to the groups inclusion of commissioners 
who later worked for law and accounting firms that had insurance 
companies as clients 
insurance commissioners are appointed or elected to state boards 
to regulate insurance rates allocate insurance premium taxes and 
carry out other duties 
this study doesnt contain any evidence of impropriety by 
insurance commissioners noted richard yingling president of the 
national association of professional insurance agents 
but even the potential for the appearance of conflict can 
erode the publics confidence in state regulation of insurance 
he added 
the study tracks the employment patterns of 55 former and 51 
current commissioners from the 50 states and the district of 
columbia who are or have served from 1984 through 1989 
employment information was obtained for 53 of the former 
commissioners twentysix worked for the insurance industry in some 
capacity 13 went to other government positions nine entered other 
industries or practiced noninsurance related law while five 
retired 
the consumer insurance interest group is a coalition of three 
consumer advocacy organizations the consumer federation of 
america public citizen a ralphnader founded group and the 
national insurance consumer organization 
the national association of professional insurance agents is a 
trade associaiton representing 180000 independent insurance agents 
who specialize in home auto and business insurance 
