criminal activity 
aguilar 58 the fourth federal judge indicted in the last 
decade is charged with eight felony counts several of the 
accusations against him are combined in a charge that he used his 
office as a racketeering enterprise to obstruct justice the 
first such charge against a federal judge 
if convicted he could draw up to 55 years in prison and 2 
million in fines 
defense attorney patrick hallinan said aguilars rulings as a 
federal judge in san jose since 1980 had generated consternation 
among prosecutors and caused some law enforcement officers to 
look upon him as an an enemy 
those officers he said included fbi agent thomas carlon the 
architect of this indictment and a man with a distaste for 
