the central philippines was rocked 
thursday by the strongest earthquake in the region in nearly 50 
years injuring at least 25 people shaking buildings and 
shattering windows authorities said 
the earthquake was measured at 69 on the richter scale by the 
us geological survey according to pat jorgenson a public 
affairs officer at its menlo park calif office 
philippine officials measured 20 aftershocks including one 
registering 66 
the quake was centered near camiguin island about 450 miles 
southeast of manila said bart bautista of the philippine institute 
of vulcanology and seismology 
the earthquake also was felt on cebu and negros islands about 
140 miles north of camiguin and in cagayan de oro on the northern 
tip of mindanao island bautista said 
twentytwo construction workers suffered burns when a vat of hot 
tar spilled on them at a 16story building site in cebu 350 miles 
south of here doctors said 15 were hospitalized and that one was 
in serious condition 
buildings swayed and electricity was cut in cebu the major city 
in the central visayas islands 
several others were slightly injured when a stampede broke out 
at one of the largest department stores in cebu traffic stopped as 
people ran out of homes offices and schools a power failure 
affected large parts of the city 
jorgensen said the earthquake was the strongest in the region 
since feb 4 1941 
the richter scale measures the magnitude of a quake at its 
epicenter according to ground motion as recorded on seismographs 
an earthquake of 6 on the richter scale is considered severe a 
magnitude of 7 a major earthquake capable of widespread heavy 
damage 
