one of the features of the house bill is a freeze on target 
prices for wheat and feed grains at their 1990 level minimum 
target prices for cotton and rice would be extended for 1991 
through 1995 crops 
soybean price support loan rates would be extended through 1995 
at 75 percent of an annual average for the previous five years 
excluding the high and low years 
the target prices and price support mechanisms would be 
potential targets for reduction under the bush administrations 
plan although yeutter did not spell out any details 
