builders will get the loans but at a higher interest rate a cost 
that will be passed on to consumers 
however the chairmen of both the senate banking committee and 
the house banking committee have said they oppose overhauling the 
sampl bill this year and hubbard said i am not proposing to 
amend the sampl law 
housing and urban development under secretary alfred a 
dellibovi said his department has been trying to ease the strain on 
builders by having secondary mortgage market agencies fannie mae 
and freddie mac buy development and construction loans from sampls 
but he said any relief will be limited and he urged sampls to 
develop networks of other institutions to participate in big loans 
officials of both the office of thrift supervision which 
regulates sampls and the office of the comptroller of the currency 
which regulates nationallychartered banks said the law leaves 
them with no discretion to delay the effective date of the new 
standard 
</TEXT>
