york times 35 regional newspapers and a onethird interest in the 
international herald tribune fell 63 percent to 251 million for 
the quarter reflecting decreased ad linage at the times and the 
staff reduction and delivery dealer charges 
the magazine group had an operating loss of 126 million in the 
latest quarter in contrast to an operating profit of 53 million a 
year earlier the loss was due to the structuring charge higher 
subscription promotion expenses and single copy circulation 
softness in the first quarter at family circle 
the broadcasting and information services group had an operating 
profit of 29 million in the quarter compared with 4 million a 
year earlier reflecting a writedown of firm and syndication rights 
the company had an equity loss of 251 million on its 
investment in its forest products group as a result of the charge 
for the valuation reserve it had equity earnings of 81 million 
in the same quarter a year ago 
for the year the company earned 2666 million or 339 a 
share up from 1677 million or 208 a share a year earlier 
the results included a gain of 1933 million after taxes on the 
sale of its cable tv system 
revenue for the year rose 4 percent to 18 billion from 17 
billion 
