<TEXT>
autoworkers ended a weekold strike at ford 
motor cos plant in the northern border state of chihuahua after 
the company agreed to a more than 27 percent pay hike ford said 
thursday 
the wage increase ranks among the largest obtained in collective 
bargaining contract negotiations in the country said fidel 
velazquez head of the mexican labor federation 
company and union negotiators for the plants 800 hourly 
employees reached a contract agreement late wednesday said ford 
spokesman al chambers in detroit they are back at work 
chambers said 
the workers contract expired jan 31 and the union went on 
strike feb 1 when the company refused to change its offer of a 12 
percent increase 
the plant produces 1300 fourcylinder engines daily for export 
to us and canadian markets 
in another labor dispute at cuautitlan near mexico city ford 
sent out about 400 layoff notices wednesday to workers who refused 
to answer a backtowork order according to the newspaper 
excelsior 
ford has announced it will fire 2200 cuautitlan union 
dissidents for failing to return to their jobs 
the company closed the plant a month ago after more than 150 
thugs beat and shot workers one union dissident was killed and 
nine were injured in the violence which ford said stemmed from an 
intraunion dispute 
authorities have issued a warrant for the arrest of cuautitlan 
official union head hector uriarte alleging that he masterminded 
the violence 
the dissidents saying that uriarte was imposed on their union 
by velazquez federation have picketed the plant continuously 
since the violence they said they would not go back to work unless 
free union elections could be held and ford could guarantee plant 
security 
the dissidents charged that the union acted in cahoots with the 
company in the labor conflict 
velazquez promised elections after unionists return to work 
saying that his federation would not try to block detention of 
uriarte 
fords cuautitlan facility produces 450 cars and trucks daily 
for the mexican market under normal conditions 
over 1000 workers are on the job making possible the 
production of only about 40 vehicles a day ford says 
