october 
last years plunge was triggered by the failure of the 74nation 
international coffee organization to agree on new export quotas to 
support prices with no agreement coffeeproducing nations battled 
for market share by offering coffee at lower and lower prices 
clearing out much of their stocks in the process 
analysts say the tightening of supplies is one factor 
underpinning the markets recent strength others include suspected 
damage to the central american crop from a christmastime freeze a 
spell of hot dry weather in brazil that threatens the quality of 
the crop there and president bushs upcoming visit to colombia 
the secondlargest coffee producer where prospects for a new 
international coffee agreement are expected to be discussed 
