omaha neb president bush told a corncountry audience 
thursday that he hopes a trade agreement with the soviet union can 
be negotiated by the time of his summer summit with soviet 
president mikhail s gorbachev expanding markets for american 
exports and helping the soviet union 
bush talked of his hopes for a trade agreement a goal he and 
gorbachev set in their meeting at malta last december in a state 
keenly interested in selling grain to the soviets 
this will relax trade barriers between east and west 
expanding markets for american exports he said in remarks to a 
1000aplate fundraising breakfast for republican gov kay orr 
i feel strongly that selling our grain to the soviet union is 
in americas interest as well as theirs he told more than 500 
people attending the breakfast 
bush also said he will push for a farm bill this year that 
emphasizes marketoriented farm policies that would give 
farmers more flexibility over what crops they grow 
whats good for agriculture is good for america he said 
us trade representative carla hills said wednesday the 
administration hoped to complete by early may a ussoviet trade 
pact that bush and gorbachev could sign at their scheduled summit 
meeting a month later 
the opening round of talks on what would be the first attempt 
