<TEXT>
ford motor co began a new incentive program 
thursday offering consumers a combination of a cash rebate and 
lowinterest financing on escort and tracer subcompact cars 
in the past automakers have offered car buyers a choice of 
either cash or low interest rates 
in the new program buyers of 1989 and 1990 escorts and tracers 
may choose a combination of either 750 or 1000 in cash 
depending on the model and 69 percent financing alternately 
customers may choose to take a cash rebate with no lowinterest 
financing of 1500 on the tracer or 1000 on the escort 
while varying the interest and rebate packages available on 
various models ford isnt greatly changing the amount it spends on 
buyer incentives spokesman jim mccraw said overall they tend 
to remain approximately the same 
in all 22 lincoln mercury and ford products are covered in the 
new program which expires april 2 
