a federal judge handed georgiapacific 
corp a victory in its bid to buy great northern nekoosa corp 
ruling thursday that it will take just a twothirds vote by great 
northern shareholders to oust the paper companys directors 
great northerns bylaws called for a threefourths vote but 
us district judge gene carter agreed with georgiapacific that 
the higher number ran afoul of maine corporate law 
the judge also struck down two other portions of great 
northerns bylaws which allowed outgoing directors to name a new 
board and called for a 90day nomination period for new directors 
were disappointed and we certainly are going to study what 
he had to say and then well decide how to react to it great 
northern spokesman stephen m hill said from his office in norwalk 
conn where the company is based it is incorporated in maine 
great northerns board has been fighting the 38 billion 
takeover attempt but georgiapacific succeeded in forcing a 
special shareholders meeting scheduled for march 2 in portland at 
which the great northern directors could be thrown out 
hill declined to predict whether great northerns directors 
would be able to survive the shareholders meeting 
atlantabased georgiapacific contends that great northerns 
directors are resisting the takeover offer so they can hold onto 
their highpaying jobs at the expense of shareholders 
despite thursdays setback for great northern the company still 
hopes to persuade carter to block georgiapacifics effort to oust 
the great northern board 
the judge plans to hear oral arguments monday on that motion by 
great northern which also hopes to block the hostile tender offer 
on grounds that include allegations that georgiapacific has 
violated federal securities laws by covering up plans to sell maine 
assets should the deal go through 
t marshall hahn jr georgiapacifics chairman and chief 
executive officer issued a statement hailing the ruling 
this is one more important advance in bringing georgiapacific 
closer to completing this acquisition which we believe is best for 
great northern shareholders employees and communities in which 
they operate hahn said 
georgiapacific has denied great northerns allegations that it 
broke the law by covering up plans to sell maine assets saying 
that it has no such plans 
