<TEXT>
the generic pharmaceutical industry 
association said thursday that it had formed a panel of independent 
experts to examine the governments drug approval process in the 
wake of the generic drug fraud and bribery scandal 
the seven medical legal and pharmaceutical experts will make 
recommendations for changes to reassure the american people that 
generic drugs are properly evaluated and safe and effective said 
lewis a engman a washington lawyer heading the committee 
there are clearly some bad apples that have been uncovered 
said engman a former chairman of the federal trade commission and 
a former president of the pharmaceutical manufacturers association 
committee members will talk to people in the generic drug 
industry and the food and drug administration and others to try 
to get a handle on the scope of these problems he said 
the scandal in the 7 billion generic drug industry became 
public last spring and led to bribery convictions of three generic 
drug company executives and bribetaking convictions of three fda 
employees 
the investigations also uncovered evidence that some drug 
companies cheated on tests required to win fda approval and 
prompted recalls of dozens of generic drugs including the 
lowerpriced versions of some popular drugs 
in one case recalls of two generic products have left 
smithkline beechams antihypertension drug dyazide one of the 
most widely prescribed drugs in the country without any generic 
competition 
bolar pharmaceutical co inc last week withdrew its version 
because it appeared false documents had been used to support the 
companys claims for the product last summer vitarine 
pharmaceuticals inc withdrew its generic from the market last 
summer after admitting it substituted samples of the brandname 
drug for its product in potency tests 
in another development thursday an fda source said bolar 
temporarily suspended distribution of all products last friday 
while company officials discusses with the fda a list of products 
the agency wants to audit 
the products are narrow therapeutic range drugs which work 
within a smaller range of potency than most drugs the source said 
bolar officials did not return telephone calls seeking comment 
jere goyan a committee member who headed the fda from 197981 
and is now dean of the school of pharmacy at the university of 
california in san francisco said he does not believe there is a 
major flaw in the fdas process for approving generic drugs 
all of the drugs that have gone through the approval process 
that havent been switched have certainly measured up and are 
therapeutically equivalent to the innovator product he said 
the committee hopes to complete its work within six months he 
said 
the fda and the justice department are continuing their 
investigations into generic drug approvals as is a house 
subcommittee which uncovered the original evidence of impropriety 
a committee within the department of health and human services 
which includes fda is conducting review of fda operations 
